<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p>Fortune! prosperity! This is the 12th year of Kōvirājakesarivarman. To Mahādeva (<foreign>mahadeva</foreign> &gt; <foreign>mahādeva</foreign>) of Tiruvālantuṟai of Ciṟupaḻuvūr, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> of Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam, Aṭikaḷ Paḻuvēṭṭaraiyar Maṟavaṉ Kaṇṭaṉār, as long as the sun and the moon endure, for one <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> of <foreign>ghee</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>neykku</foreign></supplied> with a <foreign>nārāyam</foreign> [measure], every day <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nicata</foreign></supplied> for one <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>oru</foreign></supplied> sacred lamp <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tiruviḷakku</foreign></supplied> to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eriya</foreign></supplied> day and night <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>iravum pakalum</foreign></supplied>, gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaitta</foreign></supplied> 90 undying and non-ageing <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>cāvāmūvā</foreign></supplied> great goats <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>perāṭu</foreign></supplied>. This is under the protection of the Panmāheśvaras.</p></div>

